In a major rebuff to the Soviet Union's scientific establishment, Soviet

physicists Friday nominated Nobel laureate Andrei D. Sakharov to run as a candidate in nationwide parliamentary elections scheduled for March.
Sakharov Supported During secret balloting Friday at the prestigious Lebedev Institute, the physicists supported Sakharov's candidacy by a vote of 1,543 to 22.
'Far From Delighted' "I am far from being delighted about all the things that have happened in our country over the last year.
Sakharov, who acted as an unofficial Kremlin envoy to the troubled Transcaucasian region last month, said he was particularly dismayed by a government crackdown against leading Armenian nationalists.
